6:
Our annual holiday giveaway is
coming to a close! We're counting
on you for that last push!
10:
Well that certainly went by in a
flash... Another year, another holiday
season over.
18:
It's nothing. I was just talking to
myself.
24:
Hehehe. Happy holidays to you too.
Have you been a good boy this year?
35:
Looks like we found another fan of
yours, Aperio.
42:
If you don't mind me asking, how did
you become friends with a dragon,
Miss Bianca?
45:
Well... I came across this grimoire in
the estate where I used to live. When
I opened it, Aperio just
materialized—I'd summoned him
accidentally, you see.
47:
Back then, I didn't really have any
friends. All I had was books to keep
me company. I was a voracious
reader.
50:
I-I also love books! I can relate to
them more than people...
53:
So why are you interested in
becoming friends with a dragon?
56:
I mean, if I had a dragon for a friend
that's all I would need... I wouldn't
have to bother dealing with people
anymore.
58:
Other kids think I'm weird, so they
don't want to be around me either...
But my mom just tells me to make
friends with them anyway...
60:
If that's the type of person your
mom is, I'm not sure she'd approve
of you becoming friends with a
dragon either.
65:
I do. But here's the thing...
It's entirely up to you who you want
to be friends with—or who you want
to avoid.
67:
Humans, dragons, it doesn't matter.
Only you have the power to make
that decision.
77:
Though you might not have a
choice this time—Aperio seems to
have taken a liking to you.
79:
R-really?! I-I also want to be his
friend!
85:
Aperio says he wants to see you
again.
88:
I'll definitely come by again! Thank
you for everything, Miss Bianca! I'll
see you soon too, Aperio!
91:
How curious. You open up
substantially whenever Aperio
comes into the picture.
95: Hush. Or I'll tie you up into a knot.
100:
Aren't you a little too old to be lining
up back there for Santa? You're such
a weirdo.
101:
Hey, what's that? Let me take a peek
at what you got!
104:
Huh? What's with the fuss? We're
friends, right?! So quit whining and
hand it over!
107:
A quarrel among children... But I
can't just stand back and watch this
happen. I'll go break this up.
112:
Wait a minute. I have another idea.
Aperio, could you go help our new
friend?
123:
Wh-whoa! What's with the lizard?!
That thing's freaky... Perfect for a
weirdo like you!
127:
Aperio's my friend now, and I won't
let you make fun of him! Get lost!
134:
Yeah, you tell him! We knew you had
what it takes!
146: Aperio sure seems to be having fun.
150:
The two of you make quite the
formidable team. I wonder...
156:
Anyway, we only have a couple
more presents to go through before
we're finished. Let's get to it, Bianca.
159:
Can I be myself, even if that means
I'm not your typical Santa?
162:
Yes, why not?
...There clearly seems to be demand
for your particular brand of Santa.
168:
Well then, I suppose it's time for me
to do what I do best.
171:
Line up, my cute little pets! I've got
all kinds of wonderful presents to
give out!
